        "heading_c4Vtt3": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "How and why is it different?",
            "heading_tag": "h2"
          }
        },
        "richtext_Ym9n7G": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>\"Kikumatsu's konjac can be eaten raw,\" they advertise.<br/>This means that it has very little of the \"bad smell\" or \"bitterness\" that is common in konjac, and can be eaten as is after just rinsing it with water.</p><p>There are various reasons why Kikumatsu's konjac is of such high quality, including the raw materials and coagulants.<br/>All of this requires time, effort, and manufacturing techniques, but<br/>after much trial and error, we have established a system that allows us to provide a stable supply.<br/>We will explain some of these with photos.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
